A connection with succedo was at least sometimes assumed; as by Nonius (170, 25 M.): Suc- cidiam, successionem necessariam, quoting this place. —19. conditi- ora: cf. condita, 10, 3.—19. facit: becomes passive in English, as inversion of the voice is necessary, that an effective order of words may be kept. —2o. supervacaneis . operis: ‘by spare-hour occu- pations,' with some suggestion of employments held in reserve,— not required by the routine of the estate. Hunting was a favorite sport of the Romans.
